11. triumviralibus (s): the stress reminds us that he was flogged as a slave by the triumviri capitales.

praeconis (ps) i.e. till even the praeco was tired of it; much more the flagellator. The praeco was said to go on proclaiming the culprit's offences.

15. sedilibus...eques: for the grouping see on P. 14.

‘cot ora navium...rostrata: for the order see on P. 48.
